{"updated_at": "2013-08-06T16:55:58Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2013-08-06T16:55:58Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/22193847", "id": 22193847, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/11768", "issue_id": 11768, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/thedarkone", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "c203190318ed9534390c93d1744a6cf1", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/c203190318ed9534390c93d1744a6cf1?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F68e4593563e1b425a7717504bca103d6.png", "id": 15688, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/events{/privacy}", "login": "thedarkone", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/followers"}, "body": "No, don't change the `Digestor#digest` API, if it returns an empty string (upon catching and swallowing `ActionView::MissingTemplate`) then we should cache it.\r\n\r\nThe code in `Digestor.compute_and_store_digest` shouldn't care about what kind of errors `Digestor#digest` might raise, it just needs to make sure that if it \"pre stores\" a dummy value in the `@@cache` it gets removed if something goes wrong.\r\n\r\nWhat I want is to replace the clever `ensure` block in `Digestor.compute_and_store_digest` with a simpler `rescue` block in my comment above. Also don't check the returned `digest` for presence and cache it anyway.\r\n\r\n", "_id": {"$oid": "5237d15ebd3543c151007dc4"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/11768#issuecomment-22193847"}
